<TITLE> Stock end flat on opening day </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 10 (bdnews24.com)Markets ended nearly flat on the opening day of the week with gainers dominating the day. The trading started an hour behind schedule as a mark of respect for the prime minister's husband Dr M A Wazed Miah who died on Saturday. Sunday's trading saw a sharp increase in the beginning but some issues fell afterwards mainly due to ex-dividend trade of Bank Asia and Al-Arafah Islami Bank. Market drivers banks' movement was slow with most of the issues edging up while non-banking financial institutions and insurers made significant gains. Mutual fund went down on profit-taking after Thursday's gains. ICT, fuel and energy shares had a good day with power scrips slightly going down and textile shares closing mixed. DSE's benchmark general index or DGEN witnessed volatile movement across the day. It ended slightly lower by 4.57 points or 0.18 percent to 2489.01. The DSI or all share price index ended on 2074.86, slipping 3.58 points or 0.17 percent. The blue-chip DSE-20 crept up 1.62 points or 0.08 percent to finish on 1926.66. Gainers outnumbered losers 158 to 74 while eleven issues held steady. Turnover on the country's premier bourse clocked Tk 4.79 billionslightly up from Thursday's Tk 4.36 billion. Titas Gas emerged as the turnover leader with shares worth Tk 1.47 billion traded. It gained 2.35 percent to Tk 544. Summit Power followed with a turnover of Tk 489.929 million to edge down 0.58 percent on Tk 1394.50. Beximco ended on Tk 277, slipping 0.14 percent. It had shares worth Tk 313.828 million traded. Eastern Housing Ltd had shares worth Tk 184.967 million traded and ended on Tk 706, up 3.17 percent. Bangladesh Online saw turnover worth Tk 150.368 million to rise 4.11 percent and close at Tk 119. Among the other scrips on the turnover boardBextex Ltd, S Alam Cold Rolled Steels and Shinepukur Ceramics fell on selling pressurefinished lower selling pressure. Beximco Synthetics and Beximco Pharmaceuticals rose higher. Indices on the Chittagong Stock Exchange finished slightly upbeat. The CSCX or selective categories index gained 1.29 points or 0.24 percent to close at 5297.74. The CASPI or all share price index ended on 8175.43, edging up 1.29 points or 0.02 percent. The CSE-30 blue-chip rose 18.24 points or 0.28 percent to finish at 6360.93. Of the traded issues, 87 advanced, 62 declined with seven scrips unchanged. Titas Gas topped the turnover board with shares worth Tk 71.44 million changing hands. AB Bank, Summit Power, Bextex Ltd, and Beximco Pharmaceuticals were the other turnover leaders. Turnover crept down to Tk 541.470 million from Tk 552.858 million from the previous day.
